methods.name: init
methods.desc:
Initialize the application (creator only).
Call after creation and funding to create boxes and set the TSS address. Once initialized, the contract cannot be re-initialized.

methods.name: update
methods.desc: Update the application if it is mutable (manager only)

methods.name: set_immutable
methods.desc: Set the contract as immutable (manager/creator only)

methods.name: validate_manager
methods.desc:
Fail if the sender is not the protocol manager.
To be used by the TSS to allow manager-only functions

methods.name: noop
methods.desc: No operation, use to make dummy app calls to increase opcode budget

methods.name: deposit
methods.desc:
Deposit funds.
If successful, will store a deposit receipt in a box named after the commitment; the box must be passed in. Call `insert_commitment` method afterwards to insert the commitment

methods.name: withdraw
methods.desc:
Withdraw funds.
The optional argument `no_change` is used to instruct the contract to not add the change to the tree; this is meant to be used when the tree is full. If used and the user does not withdraw the full amount available, the change will be lost.
The optional argument `extra_txn_fee` is used to indicate that the user wants to pay that as additional transaction fee to the blockchain on top of the minimum fee (e.g., if there is congestion). This amount will be subtracted from the withdrawal amount. This can be useful when calling the TSS (treasury smart signature) to pay the transaction fees.
